<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1436,191,738]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,343,671,697]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Etymology:</emphasis>
The trivial name is a Latin compound name formed from 
<emphasis box="[1021,1109,672,697]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">truncus</emphasis>
(= cut off) and 
<emphasis box="[1292,1352,672,697]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">antia</emphasis>
(= forlock). I refer to the highly setose and truncated condition of the elytral apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
